featured_reviews.review_id:
The Masjid is situated to the left of the road near sikandari Darwaza.
The minaret, about 65 feet high and 13 feet in diameter, is built in Persian style and is identical in form with the Chand Minar at Daulatabad erected in 1445 A.D by Ala-ud-din Bahmani and the minaret of the famous college of Mahmud Gawan at Bidar built during 1472 A.D. It consists of two storeys; each furnished with windows and surrounded by projecting galleries girded with stone balustrades, gradually tapers from bottom to top and has, at the top, a round dome in the Bahmani style.
Apart from its architectural peculiarities, the mosque, as the inscriptions in the building show, is the oldest place of Muslim worship in the town.

featured_reviews.review_id:
A mosque with simple structure and serene atmosphere it has ample space and maintained well, located at Haji colony Raichur, the mosque was built in 1992 by a gujrati business man janab late Abdul Ghaffar Sait in memory of his mother,
Mrs Fatima hence the name of the mosque Fatima Masjid, the mosque is well looked after and maintained by the son of janab Abdul Ghaffar Sait janab Sikandar Sait, the present imam of the masjid janab Mohammed Nizamuddin is serving as imam of the masjid since 1994, he has imparted quality service and guided many children and adults alike towards the better understanding of Islam.

This mosque was built by king Ali Adil Sha of Bijapur it was constructed during 908 hijri this date is supported by the tablets which are found in the mosque one is on the right side of the mosque and the other two one above the other on left side. This is a very big structure and one of the largest mosque in Raichur. The mosque was renovated several times and also extended length and breadth wise. The mosque is maintained by a committee comprising of local people headed by a elected president.
